    "chemicalDescription": [
      "sh-Polypeptide-85 is a single chain synthetic human peptide produced by fermentation in  E. coli.  The starting gene is a synthesized copy of the human gene which codes for Fibroblast Growth Factor 9 used as such or adapted to the production host. It contains a maximum of 208 amino acids which may contain disulfide bonds and/or glycosylation. The protein consists of the proper sequence of the 20 standard amino acids."
